		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Syracuse N. Y.</placeName> <date>August 2<hi rend="sup">nd</hi> 1852</date></p>
				<p>My dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Several months have now<lb/> passed over since I left your City&#44; when<lb/> you promised me&#44; that upon my producing<lb/> such proofs of my innocence of the Charges<lb/> laid at my door by the <hi rend="underline">kind prelate</hi> <persName>Mr Leeser</persName><lb/> that you among the rest would see that justice<lb/> should be tend to me&#8212;the necessary <hi rend="underline">Documents</hi><lb/> Testimonials&#44; and satisfactory statements have<lb/> long since been forwarded to your excellent<lb/> Minister the <persName>Revd Mr Lyons</persName>&#8212;Up to this<lb/> date I have received <hi rend="underline">no</hi> satisfaction in any<lb/> <hi rend="underline">shape</hi> or <sic>m<hi rend="underline">an</hi>ner</sic>.  Determined not to let this<lb/> matter drop into oblivion in justice to my <hi rend="underline">own</hi><lb/> reputation&#44; and <hi rend="underline">that</hi> of my family&#8212;I think it<lb/> my duty to trace the Cause of the silence of the<lb/> folks of <placeName><sic>Charlestone</sic></placeName>&#33;  I wish to prevent a Suit<lb/> at Law&#44; which I shall be compelled to institute<lb/> unless the Congregation of your City will exercise<lb/> their prerogative to be the adjudicators in this matter<lb/> between me and <persName>Mr Leeser</persName>.  I ask it now at<lb/> your hands&#8212;I have written a letter on the subject<lb/> to your worthy President and other Gentlemen who<lb/> were made parties to the affair&#8212;my injuries were<lb/> of a two fold nature.  Defamation of character<lb/> to myself&#44; and a pecuniary injury to my family&#33;<lb/>  I have therefore to request the favor at your hands<lb/> to see that I receive <hi rend="underline">Justice</hi> in the cause&#8212;and in<lb/> the Hope of your early Reply&#8212;Believe me<lb/> yours faithfully</p>
				<p><persName role="author">H. A. Henry</persName></p>
				<p><persName>S. Vallentine Esq</persName><lb/> <placeName>Charleston<lb/> S. C.</placeName></p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
			<p rend="indent(6)"><persName>S. <sic>Wallentine</sic> Esqr</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(6)"><placeName>Charleston S.C.</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">Pr favr of</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)"><persName>Mr D Jacobs</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">Present.</p>
		</body>
